"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043006","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-22","<p>While we condemn the violent behaviour of some protestors, and unlawful acts such as arson and looting, we are deeply concerned that Zimbabwe’s security forces have acted disproportionately in response. In particular, there are disturbing reports of use of live ammunition, intimidation and excessive force. On 17 January I summoned the Zimbabwean Ambassador to highlight our concern at the ongoing situation in Zimbabwe.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-01-22T15:10:31.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043006/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043006/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-17","Zimbabwe: Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of reports of recent violence in Zimbabwe.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","209728"
