"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043018","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-01-24","<p>The consultation ‘Single use carrier bags: extending and increasing the charge’ has been published and will close on 22 February.</p><p> </p><p>Consultations on reforming the packaging producer responsibility system, the introduction of a deposit return scheme and improving household and business recycling will be published shortly.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-01-24T09:42:34.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043018/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1043018/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-01-17","Waste Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to publish his consultations on the proposals in the resources and waste strategy.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","209795"
